Plugins:
    * don't throw exceptions, but use the logging facility to report exceptions and
      correct them

Other classes:
    * throw exceptions, main webgen class (presumably WebSite) catches and handles them
      (logs them and corrects them)

Plugin infos hash keys:
    * :instantiate -> controllers whether a plugin object will be instantiated
    * :is_base_plugin -> if set than the plugin class does not get registered by a PluginLoader


* Configuration file syntax:

  plugin 'Core/FileHandler' do
    param 'ignorePaths', ['**/CVS']
    meta_info({
      'indexFile' => 'test'
    }, :merge | :update)
  end

  -----
  oder:
  -----

  File/GalleryHandler:
    param1: value
    param2: [val1, val2]
    param3: {key: val}
    update_default_meta_info:
      imagesPerPage: 100
  File/PageHandler:
    default_meta_info:
      imagesPerPage: 100
  Tags/Meta:
    param: value